Czech Stocks Drop to Lowest in Two Weeks; Erste Group Bank Falls

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-06-24T13:24:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-24/czech-stocks-drop-to-lowest-in-two-weeks-erste-group-bank-falls.html
The Czech Republic’s benchmark stock
index fell for a third day to its lowest in more than two weeks
as  Erste Group Bank AG (EBS) ’s declines outweighed gains for coal
company New World Resources Plc and power utility  CEZ AS. (CEZ)   The PX gauge of companies traded down 0.1 percent to 1,209
as of 3:13 p.m. in  Prague , erasing an earlier gain of as much as
0.9 percent. The index has lost 0.6 percent so far this week.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
